parts.text:
**Asian**

**Soups:**
* Vietnamese Pho (beef or chicken noodle soup)
* Japanese Miso Soup (soybean paste broth with tofu and vegetables)
* Thai Tom Yum soup (spicy and sour soup with shrimp, mushrooms, and lemongrass)
* Korean Dolsot Bibimbap (rice bowl with various vegetables, meat, and egg in a hot stone pot)
* Indonesian Soto Ayam (chicken soup with noodles, vegetables, and hard-boiled eggs)

**Stews:**
* Japanese Nikujaga (beef and potato stew)
* Chinese Lion's Head (meatballs in gravy with vegetables)
* Korean Gamjatang (pork spine stew)
* Thai Massaman Curry (mild and creamy curry with chicken or beef)
* Vietnamese Bun Bo Hue (beef noodle soup with lemongrass and spices)

**Hot Drinks:**
* Chinese Oolong Tea (lightly oxidized tea with floral notes)
* Japanese Matcha (powdered green tea)
* Vietnamese Ca Phe Sua Da (iced coffee with condensed milk)
* Korean Sikhye (sweet rice drink)
* Thai Iced Tea (black tea sweetened with condensed milk and evaporated milk)

**Mediterranean**

**Soups:**
* Greek Avgolemono (chicken and lemon soup)
* Spanish Gazpacho (cold tomato soup with vegetables)
* Italian Minestrone (vegetable soup with pasta and beans)
* Lebanese Lentil Soup (red lentil soup with vegetables and spices)
* Turkish Yayla Çorbası (mint and yogurt soup)

**Stews:**
* Italian Osso Buco (braised veal shanks)
* Spanish Paella (seafood and rice stew)
* Greek Stifado (beef or rabbit stew with onions, tomatoes, and spices)
* Moroccan Tagine (stew cooked in a conical clay pot)
* Lebanese Kibbeh Nayeh (raw lamb or beef with spices and bulgur)

**Hot Drinks:**
* Turkish Coffee (strong, frothy coffee brewed in a cezve)
* Moroccan Mint Tea (green tea with mint leaves and sugar)
* Greek Frappe (iced coffee blended with milk and sugar)
* Italian Espresso (strong coffee brewed through a pressurized machine)
* Spanish Horchata (sweet, cold drink made from tiger nuts or rice)
